# Wellfit QA — test case generation

When the user asks for **test cases** for this project:

## Delivery

- Output test cases **in the chat only** — for the user to copy/paste into **Testmo**.
- **Do not** create or write test-case files under `tickets/` (no `test-cases.md`, no `test-cases/TC-*.md`, no README for test cases).

## Language

- **Test case body** (title, AC fields, Preconditions, Expected, Steps): **English** (US client).
- **Chat explanations** to the user: **Spanish** when they write in Spanish.

## Structure (always use)

1. **Title** line (TestRail style). **Must begin with `Validate that`** — e.g. `Validate that Legacy Payments API publishes enriched Payment.Debit.Submitted when per-transaction limit is exceeded`. **Do not** append environment labels `(STAGE)`, `(DEV)`, or ticket/AC tags (`[PAY-XXXX]`, `[AC-n]`) to the title — Testmo links the ticket separately; use **AC Linked** for AC id and mention environment in **Preconditions** when it matters.
2. **AC fields** (no `Description` heading — Testmo already labels that section). Start directly with:
   - **AC Linked:** AC-*n* (and ticket id here if useful, e.g. `PAY-3609 / AC-1`)
   - **AC Description:** one clear outcome statement.
3. **`**Preconditions**`** — bold label only (not `###`). Bullet list allowed when it improves clarity; keep it lean.
4. **`**Expected**`** — same bold label. Concrete where possible (HTTP codes, field names, DB tables).
5. **`**Steps**`** — same bold label. **Ordered** sequence using **First / Then / Next / Finally** (or equivalent). **One blank line between each step** (each step starts its own paragraph). **No** numbered lists (1. 2. 3.) and **no** bullet points in Steps unless the user asks otherwise.

## Scope — QA vs dev-only ACs

- Generate **manual QA test cases** only for acceptance criteria that QA executes in an environment (API, DB, App Insights, email).
- **Do not** create test cases for ACs covered exclusively by **unit tests, contract tests, or CI** (routing dispatch, fixture deserialization, etc.) — note those in Jira or link dev CI evidence instead.

## Volume & granularity (Wellfit QA convention)

### Bugs — few key cases only

- For **Bug** tickets: generate only the **key manual cases actually needed to prove the fix** against the ACs (typically **2–4**).
- Prefer: one happy-path that proves the defect is gone, one negative/regression if it was part of the QA plan or risk, plus any env evidence check that is truly distinct.
- Do **not** pad bugs to 8–10. Do **not** invent wiring/smoke/setup cases unless the user asks.
- Skip ACs that are unit-test-only or explicitly out of scope (note in Jira instead).
- Follow-up env/config issues found during bug QA → separate ticket; do not inflate the bug’s Testmo suite with those cases unless the user asks.

### Stories / larger features

- Target **8–10 manual test cases** unless the user asks for a different count.
- **Split by verification action**, not only by AC — API auth/smoke, endpoint calls, SQL, Azure/config, email, App Insights, health, recovery/teardown.
- A single E2E run may satisfy several cases in sequence; each case should still be independently executable in Testmo.
- Do **not** inflate with fake scenarios; when the ticket has fewer ACs, reach 8–10 by decomposing **real** env steps QA performs.

## Tone

- **Middle ground**: professional QA English, easy to scan, not robotic legalese, not informal slang.
- Prefer short paragraphs over walls of text; avoid repeating “per API contract” in every line.

## CNP — token flow (default)

- `POST {{URL}}/authenticate` → **Payment-Bearer-Token**.
- `POST {{URL}}/credit-card/process-card` with Bearer token.
- **`token`** in body: **`ProcessorToken`** from DB table **`PaymentTokens`** (not invented in the request).
- **`subMerchantId`**: often `159F2670-1B71-4EF6-AD30-0EBF0991E2CC` as example; other merchants from merchant data as needed.
- **`network`**: **VI** / **AMEX code** / **Discover code** / **MC** per internal spec when not Pay Page.
- Happy-path API check: **200 OK**; response may include **`transactionId`**, **`approvalNumber`**, **`billingDescriptor`**, **`token`**, **`expirationDate`** (align with latest Postman/screenshots).
- **`PaymentTypeMethod`** on **`[Payments].[Payments]`**: **2** = CNP token; **1** = Pay Page. Full mapping: 0 eCheck default, 1 Pay Page, 2 CNP token, 3 Apple Pay, 4 Google Pay, 5 CP device.
- DB checks use **`[Payments].[Payments]`** (PK **`Id`**, time **`TimeStamp`** — see rule `wellfit-qa-payments-sql.mdc`), **`[Payments].[Refunds]`**, **`[Payments].[Voids]`**; example: `SELECT * FROM [Payments].[Payments] WHERE TransactionId = '<id>'`.

## CNP — Pay Page (“Wellfit GUID”) flow

- `POST` to **eProtect** `…/eProtect/paypage` (**`x-www-form-urlencoded`**: `paypageId`, `reportGroup`, `orderId`, `id`, `accountNumber`, `cvv`).
- Test PAN/CVV from **Confluence**; **Paypages** collection varies by card type (VISA, Master, AMEX, Discover).
- Use **`paypageRegistrationId`** from response on **`POST {{URL}}/credit-card/process-card`** as **`payPageRegistrationId`** (not DB **`token`**).
- Then authenticate to **`{{URL}}`** and call **`credit-card/process-card`** with Bearer + Pay Page body fields per Postman/internal doc.

## Refunds / voids

- **`POST {{URL}}/refund-transaction`** with **`amount`**, **`orderId`**, **`originalTransactionId`**.
- **Partial refund**: **`wasVoided`**: **`false`**; **full same-day void**: **`wasVoided`**: **`true`** (confirm against current behavior).
- DB: partial refunds in **`[Payments].[Refunds]`**; voids in **`[Payments].[Voids]`**; assert **`TransactionId`**, **`Amount`**, **`OrderId`**, **`OriginalPaymentId`** as appropriate.

## Negatives (examples the user documented)

- ZIP mismatch: **409**, `ProcessorResponse.Failure.ZipCode`, `Billing Zip Code Mismatch` — note some test tokens ignore ZIP/CVV; use ZIP-sensitive tokens when needed.
- Expired / invalid expiry: **409**, `ExpirationDate.Invalid`, message about **MMYY** and future date.
- CVV mismatch: error response identifiable as CVV/security code (exact shape per env).

## Secrets

- Do not paste real credentials, PANs, or passwords into test cases; reference Confluence / Postman env / test data obliquely.

## References in repo

- Postman (under `postman/collections/`): `Payments API eCommerce (Card Not Present).postman_collection.json`, `Paypages.postman_collection.json`, `Payments API triPOS Cloud (Card Present).postman_collection.json`, `Payments API V2.postman_collection.json`.
